{
  "_comment": "Maps a SimpleFIN brokerage transaction's security NAME (from the tx description/payee) to a ticker, so sf:pull can type security trades as BUY/SELL. Matching is case-insensitive substring on a normalized string (uppercase; . , & ® ™ collapsed to spaces). Order matters: first match wins, so put more-specific substrings first. Extend this as new securities appear. Unmapped names are left as ordinary cashflow (never guessed) so transfers/interest aren't misread as trades.",
